This paper is primarily focused on the deployment of edge computing infrastructure in a real-world Wi-Fi network, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also utilizes optimization algorithms and load balancing techniques, which are commonly used in the field of computer science and engineering (cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.DC). Additionally, the paper addresses practical limitations such as budget constraints and hardware requirements, which are relevant to the field of computer engineering (cs.CE).
